### Relevant Information Extracted:

**Title**: COM – RFID/NFC Community – SAINTCON

**Description**:  
RFID/NFC can be a difficult technology to understand. Come learn how!  
We can help you discover how short-range wireless communication through RFID works and how you can take advantage of it or secure it. We can help you explore various tools and techniques to read/store/replay/sniff/scan/bruteforce RFID systems.

**Image**:  
![RFID 2023 Wallpaper](http://www.saintcon.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/RFID-2023_5K_Wallpaper.png)

**Brought to You By**:  
Iceman and Gobo42

**Learning Opportunities**:  
- Direct learning through hands-on CTF challenges from beginner to advanced levels.
- Understanding the operational aspects of Long Range HF readers.
- Exploring the impact of RFID technology in consumer devices such as car keys.
- Identification of security shortcomings within RFID systems.

**Tools Covered**:
- Proxmark3
- Chameleon Ultra
- Flipper Zero

**What to Bring**:
- Laptop (optional)
- RFID cards for investigation (optional)
- RFID reading devices (optional)
- Loaner gear available on a first-come, first-served basis.

**Hours of Operation**:
- **Monday**: Closed
- **Tuesday**: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday**: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Thursday**: 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Friday**: 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**What You Will Learn**:
- Functionality of RFID/NFC technology.
- Reading basic NFC tags.
- Usage of the Flipper Zero for RFID/NFC attacks.
- Understanding vulnerabilities in RFID/NFC systems.
- Evaluating your own NFC/RFID systems for vulnerabilities.

**MiniBadge Details**:  
Visit the community booth for more details on how to obtain the MiniBadge.

**Community Features**:  
- Desktop wallpaper available for download.  

